recipe.label: Lamb or Chicken Biryani Recipe
ingredientLines: 6 finely sliced medium onions (about 6 cups), divided
1 1/2 pounds cubed lamb shoulder (see note above)
2 hot green chilies (such as Serrano or Thai)
1 tablespoon grated fresh garlic (about 3 medium cloves)
2 tablespoons toasted and ground cumin seeds, divided
2 tablespoons toasted and ground coriander seeds, divided
2 inch piece of cinnamon broken into shards
1 cup fresh cilantro leaves, chopped, divided

recipe.label: Lamb Biryani
ingredientLines: 1 (4 inch [10 cm]) piece ginger, peeled and grated
4-6 green Thai, serrano, or cayenne chiles, stems removed
¼ cup (50 g) fresh mint, chopped
2 pounds (1 kg) boneless lamb leg or shoulder, cut into 1-inch (3 cm) cubes
3 medium yellow or red onions, peeled and very thinly sliced
4 tablespoons (59 mL) canola or vegetable oil
½ teaspoon (2.5 mL) saffron strands soaked in 2 tablespoons (30 mL) milk (optional)
